main_2527975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gqr1665702667631.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gqr1665702667631.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gqr1665702667631.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gqr1665702667631\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Field-Level Processing\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gqr1665702667631__field_level_processing_134386\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Field-level processing involves the current field. Many events at higher levels affect what happens to fields, such as storing data in, or retrieving data from the database. This is normal, but you should not reverse this process in an attempt to influence higher-level processing from field level.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gqr1665702667631__p_d43289e1_d43290e1_d43291e1\">You can use field-level triggers to script behavior such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gqr1665702667631__li_d21650e1_d21651e1_d21652e1\">Temporarily converting the format of data in a field (formatToDisplay and formatFromDisplay triggers)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gqr1665702667631__li_d21653e1_d21654e1_d21655e1\">Encrypting and decrypting data when storing and retrieving data in a database (formatToDbms and formatFromDbms triggers)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gqr1665702667631__li_d21656e1_d21657e1_d21658e1\">Validating the content of modified fields (validate and validateKey triggers)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gqr1665702667631__li_d21659e1_d21660e1_d21661e1\">Responding to user requests, such as pressing a button, moving the cursor into or out of a field, starting to modify a field. In form components, such requests are often handled via structure editor functions. In dynamic server pages, they are handled by interactive triggers.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sgg1707716812995.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Triggers</a><p>Triggers are script modules that are executed in response to Uniface-recognized events and commands. Uniface recognizes three types of triggers—system triggers, interactive triggers, and web triggers.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Field-Level Processing Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Field-Level Processing Field-level processing involves the current field. Many events at higher levels affect what happens to fields, such as storing data in, or retrieving data from the database. This is normal, but you should not reverse this process in an attempt to influence higher-level processing from field level. You can use field-level triggers to script behavior such as: Temporarily converting the format of data in a field (formatToDisplay and formatFromDisplay triggers) Encrypting and decrypting data when storing and retrieving data in a database (formatToDbms and formatFromDbms triggers) Validating the content of modified fields (validate and validateKey triggers) Responding to user requests, such as pressing a button, moving the cursor into or out of a field, starting to modify a field. In form components, such requests are often handled via structure editor functions. In dynamic server pages, they are handled by interactive triggers. Related Links Triggers Triggers are script modules that are executed in response to Uniface-recognized events and commands. Uniface recognizes three types of triggers—system triggers, interactive triggers, and web triggers. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}